'''Mel Achy''' is the author of the [[Big book of bangs|Big Book of Bangs]]. In it, they detail all the explosive reactions that they encountered in their travels.{{CiteText |text=Big book of bangs |author=Mel Achy |quote=In my travels, I have witnessed many explosive creations.}}

They have travelled to the "far east", although which region this would encompass is not known. There they found a recipe for a mix dubbed "fire oil", made from quicklime, brimstone and naphta.{{CiteText |text=Big book of bangs |author=Mel Achy |quote=One of particular notes, is fire oil. Used in the far east, fire oil has an incredible explosive capability. However, it also sticks to anything it touches. [...] The quicklime, sulphur, naphtha and{{sic}} can be mixed at any time.}}

At some point, [[Lord Iorwerth]] came to possess Mel Achy's book. As he didn't have the troops available to take on [[King Tyras]]'s forces directly, Lord Iorwerth suggested to the [[Player character|adventurer]] to create a bomb to assassinate Tyras, using the knowledge found in the book.{{CiteNPC |npc=Lord Iorwerth |loc=Regicide |quote=Good job. As we don't have the troops available to take on his forces directly, I suggest we try some alternative tactics. I have this book here which details an explosive reaction. We should be able to use it to create a bomb.}}

==Trivia==
* Mel Achy is an anagram of "alchemy".

